      "number": 1,
      "title": "离 — Expressing Distance",
      "explanation": "离(lí) is used to express the distance between two places or two points. Structure: Place A + 离 + Place B + 远/近(far/close). It can also be followed by a specific measurement. Note: 离(lí) cannot be replaced by 从(cóng) in this context. Examples: 我家离学校很近(My home is close to school); 这里离那里有多远?(How far is it from here to there?)",
      "examples": [
